            <h3>Bangalore</h3>


            <h4>Bangalore Palace</h4>
            <p>One of the several residences of the Wadiyar dynasty, who governed most of South India for centuries, Bangalore Palace is one of the most beautiful structures in the city.</p>


            <h4>Lalbagh Botanical Gardens</h4>
            <p>One of Bangalore's largest green spots, the huge Lalbagh Botanical Gardens is spread across 240 acres (97 hectares) of lush vegetation, flowers, and dozens of different species of birds. Its expansiveness is a major factor in the city's moniker, the Garden City.</p>


            <h4>Nandi Hills</h4>
            <p>Roughly shaped like a sleeping bull, Nandi Hills is a magnificent trekking location located approximately a 1.5-hour drive from Bangalore. This is unquestionably one of the greatest activities in Bangalore.</p>

            <h3>Goa</h3>


            <h4>Aguada Fort</h4>
            <p>Overlooking the Arabian Sea and the Mandovi River confluence is the fort. A 19th-century lighthouse and the Central Jail are located within this stunning reddish-brown fort.</p>


            <h4>Dudhsagar Waterfalls</h4>
            <p>Cascading down from a height of 310 meters, this multi-tiered, milky-white waterfall is India's fifth-highest waterfall.</p>


